Author: procrastinationtm
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: JWC Blockchain Ventures Corporation (known as JWC) is establishing the first tokenized venture fund with two missions: 1) connecting the two worlds of Venture Capital and blockchain along with other advanced technologies (such as AI, ML, Big Data) and 2) offering crypto-investors of any size a potential high return of investment through a transparent mechanism of investing in a pipeline of new disruptive opportunities in both equity and token investments. _        Market: APEC & EMEA economies. _        Fund size: up to $30M & designed as a 6-year fund: 3 years of new investments, and 3 years of follow up investments and portfolio management. _        JWC Team: Two General Partners (one in EU, one in APAC) and a team of domain experts as advisors. _        Targeted number of investments: 15. _        Typical investment: $250k-$5M, typical equity stake: 20-25%.

Author: procrastinationtm
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: - Our JWC fund's product include an investment pipeline, advisory toolset and financial consulting. So far, we had one startup in our portfolio i.e. Caganu.com (SEA vertical O2O e-commerce) - As for our technical development, JWC Lab has been working on a cross-border multi-currency wallet whose beta version to be launched in Q3/2018.

His research expertise and experience include Deep Learning, Reinforcement Learning, Optimization, Distributed Computing and AI - whose market valueis expected to reach 10.5 billion USD in 2020. At Microsoft, he led the research and development for strategic AI projects such as Project FarmBeats: AI & IoT for Agriculture, Deep Reinforcement Learning for Control Problems in Data Center Energy Optimization, Indoor Agricultureand Computer Vision API for Cognitive Services.Another meaningful project of his isSeeing AI project that create applications for people who are blind or visually impaired. Kenneth received his Ph.D. in Computational & Applied Mathematics from The University of Texas at Austin.

I made this simple scenario thinking based on condition/numbers from the whitepaper  Think about this applied scenario you invest into JWC "Ventures", they invest 250k-5m to a portfolio company for in exchange for 20-25% Ownership to JWC like stated in whitepaper, in 5-10 years one of them exits/sells the company (some others might not, or need further investment) and JWC will then receive 20-25% of the exit (in this scenario no further investment/dilution happened) and of that 20-25% profit of JWC, 20% will be used to buy back JWC tokens for unknown price and process. So an exit of 5m will result in 1-1.25M profit for JWC and 20% of that profit (if not reinvested, spent) 200k-250k will be avaible to buy back JWC coins for unknown price and process. So wait 5-10 years hope for exit and then hope further to be one of the lucky to sell JWC, or reinvest your JWC into maybe sub coins in a never-ending cycle Roll Eyes  4. If it works out nice, I mean stealing everyones IP and reusing it right? 5. The fund portfolio consist of team members of JWC, so raising for there own projects. Diversification makes it much more difficult to succeed/exiting one as complexity rises non linear (Venture capital investing, logistic, O2O, Nanotechnology, etc) 6. cool got crypto wallets

Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: The JWC fund are allocated as follows: • 10% (150,000,000) to be sold by JWC to presale purchasers pursuant to a Future Tokens Agreement (“FTA”) offering or through JWC Whitelisted Investors. • 70% (1,050,000,000) to be sold by JWC to ICO purchasers. ICO round will last from Jan 23 to Feb 11, 2018 • 8% (120,000,000) to be reserved by the Company to Advisors and strategic partners. • 12% (180,000,000) to be distributed by the Company to the JWC Team and community supporters. The token distribution for JWC Team and Advisor is locked by “smart contracts”, 20% after completion of the token sale and other 20% on 6-month cliffs, fully disbursed after 2 years.

Author: procrastinationtm
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: With a Smart Business Contract platform specifically optimized for e-commerce, and common data services such as personal identify and credit history on the blockchain, the JWC blockchain is ideally suited for many types of e-commerce applications. If a blockchain application is going to be built on JWC blockchain, it will utilize the JWC as its means to pay for the execution of Smart Business. Contracts and settlement of financial transactions. The application could also issue its own tokens in an Initial Coin Offering to support its own unique features and community. Just as Ethereum-based applications use the ETH as the basis to issue ERC20 tokens in ICOs, e-commerce applications could use the JWC as the basis (i.e., master token) to issue their own ICO tokens.

Author: procrastinationtm
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: - The General Partner and the JWC Fund are both recently formed and have no or limited operating history. There can be no assurance that investors will recover their invested capital. - The JWC Fund will lack sectorial diversification and, as a consequence, the aggregate return on investment in the JWC Fund may be substantially or completely adversely affected by the unfavorable performance of the e-commerce sector. - In some cases, conventional valuation methods may be inappropriate or impossible to employ. There is no assurance that the valuation obtained by the JWC Fund for any investment will be able to provide returns for investors. - The General Partner, the Fund Manager, and their affiliates may engage in a broad spectrum of investment and consulting activities. - If the JWC Fund is undercapitalized and is not successful in attracting further investments in subsequent closings or if the Fund Manager is unsuccessful in launching successor funds, the JWC Fund may be forced to reduce the size of its operations, which could have an adverse impact on the ability of the General Partner and/or the Fund Manager to manage investments.

Author: procrastinationtm
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: We believe in a decentralized ecosystem that allows startup to create a tokenized product that will take advantage of the most advanced technologies. JWC Lab is a gateway for startups to innovate and benefit in such healthy ecosystem. By making the ecosystem transparent, open, and safe, applications that use blockchain technology for the decentralization and globalization of currencies can have great competitive advantages in the existing business landscape. JWC Lab’s focus is on researching and designing the right solutions based in order to boost the growth of portfolio companies and increase the value of JWC tokens by the increasing demand and adoption. The following are the key areas of R&D focus: –        Payments –        Product origin –        Trusted reviews –        Addressing the counterfeit problem –        Supply chain –        Loyalty –        Built-in smart contract modules

Author: procrastinationtm
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: We believe in a decentralized ecosystem that allows startup to create a tokenized product that will take advantage of the most advanced technologies. JWC Lab is a gateway for startups to innovate and benefit in such healthy ecosystem. By making the ecosystem transparent, open, and safe, applications that use blockchain technology for the decentralization and globalization of currencies can have great competitive advantages in the existing business landscape. JWC Lab’s focus is on researching and designing the right solutions based in order to boost the growth of portfolio companies and increase the value of JWC tokens by the increasing demand and adoption. The following are the key areas of R&D focus: –        Payments –        Product origin –        Trusted reviews –        Addressing the counterfeit problem –        Supply chain –        Loyalty –        Built-in smart contract modules

Keys will be held by Executive Directors of JWC Ventures so that all outgoing transactions must be verified by multiple parties. The crowdsale smart contract code on JWC GitHub will be public and available for audit by anyone. Exchange rates are subject to change without notice prior to the start of the public crowdsale. Once the public crowdsale starts the exchange rate will be locked. Meanwhile, the prices for the presale are not subject to change and will remain the same and have no effect on the public crowdsale.

Author: big-vados123
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: MEW itself is safe in the owner's responsibility. Infact, MEW is developed for full control and right of the owner over his wallet. There have been cases of MEW being hacked, however, only because the wallet owner was not reasonably careful enough to let hacker either have the private key or install harmful software in to victim's computer. Thus, we strongly recommend all crypto-investors (not just ours only) to store your key information in a "cold wallet" beside what you have secured in the network - the "hot wallet"

Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: We believe in a decentralized ecosystem that allows startup to create a tokenized product that will take advantage of the most advanced technologies. JWC Lab is a gateway for startups to innovate and benefit in such healthy ecosystem. By making the ecosystem transparent, open, and safe, applications that use blockchain technology for the decentralization and globalization of currencies can have great competitive advantages in the existing business landscape. Author: big-vados123
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: In JWC Venture Capital platform, JWC token acts as the base currency for startups and TGEs to establish and develop upon. In event of startup issuing its own token, TGE’s participant can use JWC to purchase the new startup token. More importantly, the startup will use JWC alongside its token in operation and daily transaction with a discount from JWC. The mechanism will incentivize higher demand for the base currency, supporting long-term increasing in its price.

Author: big-vados123
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: An investment in JWC Fund involves a number of significant risks that should be considered before making any investment. These risks include, but are not limited to, the following:  ● The General Partner and the JWC Fund are both recently formed and have no or limited operating history. There can be no assurance that investors will recover their invested capital. Although the members of the General Partner have formed and managed other funds that are similar to the JWC Fund in the past  ● The success of the JWC fund will depend on the availability of appropriate investment opportunities and the ability of the JWC Fund to identify, select, close, improve and exit those investments. There can be no assurance that there will be a sufficient number of suitable investment opportunities  ● The JWC Fund will lack sectoral diversification and, as a consequence, the aggregate return on investment in the JWC Fund may be substantially or completely adversely affected by the unfavorable performance of the e-commerce sector.  ● The JWC Fund may invest in companies that may be considered to be in early stages of growth.  ● The JWC Fund may invest in early-stage companies that do not have a clear valuation.  ● The General Partner and the Fund Manager engage in activities where its interests or the interests of its clients may conflict with the interests of the JWC Fund.  ● The General Partner is not licensed under Cayman Island or any other securities legislation  ● If the JWC Fund is undercapitalized and is not successful in attracting further investments  ● The investments may be in countries in which local regulators did or are in a process of banning or putting restrictions on cryptocurrencies, cryptocurrency exchanges and/or TGE.   Please see the https://tge.jwcventures.com/public/file/JWC-Whitepaper-v3.0.pdf

Author: big-vados123
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: The following are the key areas of R&D focus: – Payments Purchase payment in JWC tokens is conducted directly and without any middleman. The “smart contract” transfers the money to the seller’s account only when the item has reached its destination. Cashback mechanisms can be implemented when paying with JWC tokens, as well as discounts. The “smart contract” ensures that the money goes to the seller’s account only after the item has reached its destination.  – Product origin Blockchain enables transparency and feasibility for quality and convenient access by any participant to the distributed ledger database. A seller can have a crystal-clear look at their cargo shipment and at the same time the buyer is able to trace the product’s origin.  – Trusted reviews The “smart contract” records the interaction between the buyer and the seller, ensuring all reviews come from people who actually bought the item.  – Addressing the counterfeit problem One of the key features of the blockchain is the immutability of its records. This feature makes it ideal for tracking the authenticity of for-sale products. Sellers or even manufacturers/suppliers can create certificates of authenticity for products.  – Supply chain In a token-based system, transactions amongst community members may be recorded instantly and securely using digital tokens. The parties would only convert any excess tokens into other assets from time to time on an “as needed basis”, limiting transaction costs.  – Loyalty Loyalty reward system acts as a fundamental community bond, for both merchants and customers. Any user participating in the “smart contract” transaction such as e-commerce one is encouraged to exercise integrity and honesty.  – Built-in smart contract modules With a Smart Business Contract platform specifically optimized for e-commerce and common data services, the JWC blockchain is ideal for many types of e-commerce applications. If a blockchain application is going to be built on the JWC blockchain, it will utilize the JWC as its means to pay for the execution of Smart Business Contracts and settlement of financial transactions.

Author: big-vados123
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: JWC general partners have been active in the venture space for the last 6 years. As a result, we can leverage our strong insights from deal flows in APAC, EMEA and US markets.  The following is a description of the first investment initiative by JWC as a case study for the investment thesis of the fund:   Caganu.com investment case   Introduction – Founded in 2012 in HCMC (Vietnam). – Developed a vertically integrated e-commerce business with an unique O2O (online to offline) component. – Expanding its territory in Vietnam with a 2-tiered supply chain model. – Raising funds to establish three new central warehouses (HCMC, Hanoi, Danang) and 60+ satellite showrooms. – Profitable since 2014 with over 120,000 orders placed in 2016.  Target market The obtainable market is conservatively estimated at 25% of the total domestic e-commerce. Thanks to O2O and offline strategy, Caganu is capturing the opportunity of the whole e-commerce in the Vietnamese provinces along with a big part of local retail.  Validation Caganu is the leading B2C e-commerce platform for fishing equipment and leather products in Vietnam. In order to execute its plan, Caganu is planning to raise 2M USD. By completing the three central warehouses and reaching long-term profitability by 2019, we do not anticipate a need for future cash injections to finance future growth.  Potential exists Caganu has been executing its plan to meet compliance and eligibility requirements for IPO in the Vietnamese stock exchanges since the first day the company was formed. This IPO could be an interesting exit strategy for the investors. A comparable case is Thegioididong.com, which expanded nationally with a similar dealership model. In this venture, Mekong Capital invested 3.5M USD in 2007 when Thegioididong.com had only 7 stores in the country. The IPO of the Thegioididong.com in 2014 resulted in a tenfold return to Mekong Capital.

Author: big-vados123
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: Why a Tokenized Fund on Blockchain  Solving Illiquidity Problem of Startup Investment The biggest limitation of traditional venture capital (VC) model is that VC funds are not liquid. For that reason, investing in the most exciting stage of tech startups is reserved only for those who can afford to “forget” about their capital for 5-10 years. In other words, if you invested 1 million USD into a typical VC fund, you would be locking up that 1 million USD for ten to fifteen years. As a result, the VC model is currently available only for accredited investors, institutional LPs and family offices. Asset tokenization refers to taking illiquid assets and issuing tradable tokens that give holders rights in these assets (“asset-backed tokens”), resulting in improved liquidity because the assets become tradable on cryptocurrency exchanges 24/7 every day in a week.  Blockchain Funded and Cross-border Solutions JWC is the blockchain digital accelerator trusted by the crypto communities. We provide direct funding to empower companies. JWC scales up our blockchain-funded decentralized and cross-border solutions and services to create corporations with: 1) Innovative and Industry-Disruptive Solutions, 2) Efficiencies and Cost-Saving, and 3) Highly Competitiveness.  Blockchain and Financial Assets Blockchain technology now offers opportunities for gaining returns in excess of those earned by traditional venture capitalists. This technology and its impacts appear complex and daunting by most prospective investors. Therefore, JWC will be a very unique opportunity for investors, enabling them to have access to venture capital opportunities in various industry sectors.  Diversification for Crypto Investors JWC offers qualified crypto investors the option to diversify some of their cryptocurrency holdings into a portfolio of proven and growing innovative tech startups, since JWC will selectively perform equity investments in those portfolio companies.  The Value Proposition of JWC Ventures JWC offers the following set of services: Fund Management, Global Partnerships, Deal Origination and Screening, Cultural Integration, Operational Excellence, Best Practice Implementation, Optimized Exits, and Trust & Credibility.

Author: big-vados123
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: Meet our new advisor: Dr. Sheraz Majeed  Dr Sheraz Majeed is a Medicine Consultant in Ellenor Hospice in Kent. He has been working for the UK's National Health Service (NHS) for 15 years and has been teaching junior doctors and medical students. NHS shares out and distribute more than £100 billion pension funds for patients and the tax payer in England. He is the Co-Founder of Global Blockchain Consortium (GBC) involving with Blockchain Technology. He is a Cryptocurrency Advisor/Teacher. He is the keynote speaker on Blockchain use case for healthcare systems, Healthcare solutions and healthcare industry, on healthcare integrating AI, IOT and Blockchain, and on proving solutions and revolutionising Healthcare through Blockchain Technology. Future advisor and consultant on Healthcare solutions ICOs in US and Germany. https://tge.jwcventures.com/

Author: nikolayenko
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: An investment in JWC Fund involves a number of significant risks that should be considered before making any investment. These risks include, but are not limited to, the following:  ● The General Partner and the JWC Fund are both recently formed and have no or limited operating history. There can be no assurance that investors will recover their invested capital. Although the members of the General Partner have formed and managed other funds that are similar to the JWC Fund in the past  ● The success of the JWC fund will depend on the availability of appropriate investment opportunities and the ability of the JWC Fund to identify, select, close, improve and exit those investments. There can be no assurance that there will be a sufficient number of suitable investment opportunities  ● The JWC Fund will lack sectoral diversification and, as a consequence, the aggregate return on investment in the JWC Fund may be substantially or completely adversely affected by the unfavorable performance of the e-commerce sector.  ● The JWC Fund may invest in companies that may be considered to be in early stages of growth.  ● The JWC Fund may invest in early-stage companies that do not have a clear valuation.  ● The General Partner and the Fund Manager engage in activities where its interests or the interests of its clients may conflict with the interests of the JWC Fund.  ● The General Partner is not licensed under Cayman Island or any other securities legislation  ● If the JWC Fund is undercapitalized and is not successful in attracting further investments  ● The investments may be in countries in which local regulators did or are in a process of banning or putting restrictions on cryptocurrencies, cryptocurrency exchanges and/or TGE.   Please see the https://tge.jwcventures.com/public/file/JWC-Whitepaper-v3.0.pdf

Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: Here's the introduction of Matthew Brandt - JWC's Venture Investment Advisor on our official website: "Operating Partner (COO) at SILK Ventures which is a 500 million USD alignment focused on cross border investments, headquartered in London. SILK has LP, GP and Strategic agreements with SASAC Shenzhen, which has control of the 1.5 trillion USD and is the branch of the State Council’s asset control arm providing tech bridge to China. Mr. Brandt was GP / Co-Founder and Managing Director of the Global China Holdings partnering with a NYC based Family Office which had acted as principal in over 200 acquisitions and other investments totaling 3 billion USD in value with transaction sizes ranging from 2 million USD to 150 million USD. Mr. Brandt was responsible for generating proprietary China Private Equity deal flow and for all China Private Equity related oversight regarding operational value add."

Author: procrastinationtm
Title: [ANN] JWC Blockchain Ventures - The 1st Tokenized Blockchain Venture Capital
Body: Bounty | Telegram | Facebook | Twitter | LinkedIn | Whitepaper   ADVANCED TECHNOLOGY | GLOBAL LOGISTICS | BIOTECH | E-COMMERCE | SOCIAL VALUE  Providing finance, advisory and toolset service to create the highest jump for the startups.   The ongoing trends of blockchain technology applications impact many small to large corporations and are disrupting various industries. At the frontier, JWC Blockchain Ventures Corporation (JWC) establishes the first decentralized platform for tokenization service with two missions: 1) connecting the two worlds of Crowdfunding and blockchain to other advanced technologies i.e. Artificial Intelligent (AI), Machine Learning (ML), Big Data and 2) offering crypto-contributors of any size a potential high return of investment through a transparent mechanism of investing in a pipeline of new disruptive opportunities in token investments. JWC aims to be one of the most active tokenization service provider dedicated to unique blockchain solution for tech innovators that answer the needs of crypto communities and can deliver positive changes to specific industries. JWC can assist our portfolio companies to drive growth inflection in the defined markets, to deliver strategic partnerships and operational high-growth support, and to enable high value M&A, IPOs and TGEs in EMEA, APAC and US regions. JWC searches for early-stage ventures with a focus on a set of vertical industries. We provide finance, advisory and advanced technology support to help companies reach their highest potential. For our contributors, transparency is no longer a myth with JWC ecosystem, thanks to the blockchain technology.   JWC TOKEN Token Sale Utility tokens ●   Token name: JWC Blockchain Ventures ●   Platform: Ethereum ●   Token standard: ERC-20 ●   Total initial token sale supply: 1,000,000,000 JWC ●   Accepted cryptocurrency: ETH ●   Target: $30 million ●   Pre-sale fixed price 1 ETH = 10,000 JWC ●   Public sale fixed price 1 ETH = 10,000 JWC    PROJECT ROADMAP   FOUNDING TEAM & ADVISORS     TEAM EXPERIENCE   Getting started: To get started with JWC Blockchain Ventures, please visit our website at https://tge.jwcventures.com. Please feel free to send any relevant questions below and we'll reply as soon as possible.
